A giant strike is coming
The Liga trade union association, or the National Union of Workers&#39; Councils (MOSZ), will create its strike committee on Friday to coordinate Monday&#39;s indefinite strike.
A protest public meeting is being held on Saturday, and work will be stopped on Monday - the day of the final vote on the health insurance law.
The action is sure to cause serious traffic disruptions, as rail traffic will almost completely stop, and Budapest Transport Company (BKV) employees will also be on strike until 1 p.m.
On Friday afternoon, the Liga association together with the National Union of Workers&#39; Councils will present the details of the jointly organized Monday strike.
There will also be a strike committee LIGA - MOSZ, which will coordinate Monday&#39;s action.
A protest public meeting is being held on Saturday, and from Monday the unions joining the strike will stop work indefinitely unless an agreement is reached with the government.
This means that no date has been set for the end of the strike, which will begin on the day of the parliamentary vote on the health insurance law.
If Parliament ultimately fails to pass the Health Insurance Act, the unions will immediately withdraw their strike call.
However, if the legislation is voted down, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the next course of action.
According to the agenda of the Parliament meeting on Monday, it is also possible that the health insurance law will only be voted on in the late evening or at night.
Due to the strike starting on Monday, it is possible to count on serious interruptions of transport: work on the railway will be stopped for an indefinite period, part of Budapest&#39;s public transport and more than half of Volán companies may stop in the morning.
At the same time, half of the road will be closed in many parts of the country.
The strike call was joined by numerous trade unions and civic organizations, the list of which is constantly updated on the website of the Liga association.
Some organizations announced an indefinite strike, others announced a temporary work stoppage.
By Thursday afternoon, the Hungarian State Railways (MÁV) and the Independent Trade Union of Railway Employees (VDSZSZ) could not even agree on sufficient services, while more and more people are traveling by rail at the beginning of the Christmas holidays.
According to the announcements so far, there will be a strike at BKV from the start of operations until 1 p.m., from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m. at the Budapest Airport company. teachers and the Democratic Trade Union of Teachers.
The Hungarian Doctors Union will strike alternately across the country, the Democratic Trade Union of Health and Social Workers (EDDSZ), belonging to the Trade Union Cooperation Forum (SZEF), is organizing a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands formulated by the Liga association is that the government withdraw the health insurance reform proposal and present a new concept for public discussion.
The second requirement is that the new method of counting pensioners valid from next year be introduced gradually.
Thirdly, to ensure the possibility of inclusion in the system before the year 2010 for early retirement for the relevant fields of work.
The fourth reason for the action is that the Independent Trade Union of Railway Employees (VDSZSZ), which falls under the trade union Liga, does not accept the offer of the Ministry of Economy and Transport regarding the railway branches, and expects another offer.
Political Capital: The Hungarian Guard increased the country&#39;s risk
According to the Risk Analyzing Division of the Political Capital Institute, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, founded with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért movement in August of this year, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the entire region in several ways.
In the &quot;risk warning&quot; drawn up by the company, it is written: in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the biggest political risk is that &quot;by intensifying the already existing ethnic tension between the Roma and non-Roma population of Hungary, even violent ethnic clashes may occur in a short period of time&quot;.
The main reason is that the Hungarian Guard&#39;s political strategy is probably aimed at provoking such an action, the research institute adds.
As he writes, all of this can be explained by one of the greatest carelessness of Hungarian political representatives: &quot;the representatives of public life left the public discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who could build a political strategy on the Roma-Hungarian conflict.&quot;
This deepens the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts - the institute judges.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, due to the great attention of the domestic and foreign media, &quot;to a large extent spoiled the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of faith in the stability of the country and its democratic maturity&quot;.
The institute reminds: part of the reorganization of Hungarian radical and ultra-right groups, which has been receiving more and more publicity and vehemence since the fall of 2006, is that several organizations have been created in Hungary since the summer of 2007, which call themselves &quot;national militia&quot; associations.
&quot;The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil associations, while openly proclaiming - even armed - the readiness of their members to perform defensive tasks (in the event of natural disasters, attacks on the homeland, disruption of order), in addition pointing out the inability of the police, the army , or the state,&quot; he adds.
He further notes: all this is done in a way that tries to wrap all sorts of political efforts based on society&#39;s opposition to politics and parties in civilian clothes.
Emphasizing civility and the form of association in the case of these groupings is therefore not only used to avoid the legal pitfalls of court registration, but is also a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a factor increasing the risk also from the point of view of neighborly relations.
&quot;In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been pointed to in several neighboring states as a potential source of danger, the ultra-nationalist political representatives of some neighboring countries want to excuse their own anti-Hungarian policy by referring to the establishment of the Hungarian Guard.
All this can affect the political stability of the area,&quot; he adds.
According to the research institute, the emergence of the Hungarian Guard in Central and Eastern Europe is not an isolated phenomenon, so the political risks for the region as a whole have increased.
As he writes, the activity of the Hungarian Guard resembles, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard, the creation of which was announced in August 2007 by the ultra-right Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
The background to the creation of the Bulgarian Guard is the mass Roma riots that broke out in one of Sofia&#39;s districts (Krasna Poljana).
The BNU used this to establish the Guard, stating that the organization&#39;s goal was &quot;national militia&quot;.
According to her, in the past 17 years, there has been &quot;gypsy terror&quot; in Bulgaria, but the state has remained inactive and indifferent, reminds the Institute Political Capital.
He adds that the initiative has sparked a stormy discussion among the Bulgarian public.
As he goes on to write, the increase in the risk of ethnic clashes is signaled by the announcement by some Bulgarian Roma organizations that they will form their own guard as a sign of resistance.
Since the current activity of the Hungarian Guard shows similarities with the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard, it is not excluded that the Hungarian Roma will react to the threat in a similar way, by establishing their own militia, we can read in the risk warning prepared by the Political Capital Institute.
When asked by the press office, Attila Juhász, research director of the Political Capital Institute, stated: risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, they release a risk analysis every year and if they find something that could affect a change in risk, they inform the public, like in this case by issuing a risk alert.
Holidays are not free everywhere
In Hungary, days off are strictly defined by law, and it has already become common practice to move working days around holidays, which we expect less often next year.
Holidays are not uniform in the European Union or America.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and non-working days.
Days off are usually associated with church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year here: the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year is a holiday - on New Year&#39;s Day so that people can relax after New Year&#39;s Eve.
We otherwise have a total of eleven free holidays during the year.
National holidays are March 15, celebrating the 1848 revolution, and October 23, commemorating the 1956 revolution.
On August 20 we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1 we celebrate work, on November 1 and 2 we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, Easter, Pentecost and Christmas are two-day holidays.
As our public, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend according to the calendar, it has become a practice to shift the working day in cases where we only work one day before or after a holiday.
However, the price for long weekends is that we stay at work and school on the preceding Saturdays.
For many years, the Minister of Labor has regulated when we work on the day that immediately precedes or follows the holiday in a special decree.
The legal regulation applies equally to all employers and their employees, to public employees and to persons in public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or, in view of their purpose, also operate on non-working days.
This year, the work schedule will change only around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, or according to experience so far, most people will &quot;work&quot; the days between Christmas and New Year&#39;s Eve in advance or use the saved vacation in this way.
Next year, several of our holidays will fall in the middle or at the end of the week, so there will be fewer working day shifts than this year.
For the first time, the calendar will be transformed around Labor Day, so that workers can then stay at home for four days at leisure.
Saturday, April 26, will be a working day so that Friday, May 2, can be a day of rest.
Another shift is related to the holiday of October 23: work will be done on Saturday, October 18 instead of Friday, October 24.
However, the end of the year next year will be able to take place completely under the sign of holidays, because from December 24 almost everywhere will have non-stop holidays, despite the fact that New Year&#39;s Eve falls on a Wednesday.
Six creepy little things you can do to annoy your colleagues
Emails that we forget to send, voicemails that we never receive, innocent lies that we almost don&#39;t even notice anymore: all of this &quot;enriches&quot; everyday days in the workplace.
The question is, will you get used to these minor inconveniences, or will you put on your gloves and deliberately avoid unclear situations that can make others angry.
Tips.
“Sorry, I forgot to tell you that they were looking for you in the marketing department,” a colleague informs you.
That you missed the meeting because of it?
At best, he regrets it and tries to fix it, or calls the marketing department and says he forgot to deliver the message (this is a less common solution).
Most often, the matter is resolved with one apology.
Before making an awkward apology, it&#39;s a good idea to think about what you could do to make your colleagues uncomfortable, and consciously try to prevent it.
Borrowing something that isn&#39;t yours?
There&#39;s nothing more annoying than reaching for a document, an office item or your phone and it&#39;s not there.
Remember putting a stapler on your desk yesterday, but it&#39;s gone by morning?
Or have you discovered your pen that you thought was lost on the desk of one of your colleagues?
Don&#39;t take anything from your colleagues without permission, otherwise they will rightly be angry with you for digging into their things.
Don&#39;t take envelopes or sticky notes with you from the office, as it can be inconvenient if you run out of them prematurely and you need them immediately.
Gossip about the private lives of colleagues?
There is no good solution to stop the spread of gossip.
Who, with whom, what was he doing?
Where and why?
Don&#39;t hang your news (assumptions) about the private lives of colleagues on everyone&#39;s nose!
When one of them shares their innermost secrets with you, don&#39;t abuse their trust!
Lock up what you have heard and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence, even when others know about his things.
Do you report your absence without reason?
If you call the office and cite a severe headache to report your absence because you are not feeling well, or you think you would rather rest today, remember that your work, urgent tasks and work with a certain deadline are for you someone else will have to do it.
Be considerate of your colleagues!
If you know in advance that you will not be going to work the next day, or that something may happen that will require you to stay home, let your colleagues and supervisors know that you will not be confronted with your absence until the next day.
Humming, giggling, talking on the phone
Have you immersed yourself in work, only to be rudely pulled out of it by the giggles of your colleagues?
Have you accidentally overheard a phone conversation you&#39;d rather not hear at all?
Do not disturb your co-workers by humming, singing, talking loudly (over their heads), or stomping, cursing constantly, or loudly expressing your displeasure.
All this can be distracting even when they are not involved in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Do you blame others for mistakes?
If something is not on time or you forgot to send an important letter or message, don&#39;t blame others for your forgetfulness!
Do not refer to possible chaos in the office and noisy colleagues!
Admit if you made a mistake and someone paid for it, and repair the damage!
Ask how you could make things right, fix the sloppiness!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Sweatpants and slippers: comfortable clothes for home, but not suitable for the office!
Don&#39;t wear casual clothes, even if your profession allows it!
Don&#39;t be sloppy, honor your colleagues and yourself by coming to the office in casual clothes - and if your profession requires it, nice and elegant!
When a person wants to please, he ceases to be interesting
Driving around in the usual morning congestion.
A strange melody comes from the radio: the sound of a violin joined by electronic effects.
I turn up the volume.
The music changes tempo and bass is added with the previous tonal timbre, then a female choir joins in as a real gem.
On station mr2, a song by Zagar called Wings of Love is playing.
Domestic music life has not spoiled us with quality electronic pop for a long time.
But suddenly the constipation looks quite different because you&#39;re listening to Zagar&#39;s new album.
The emergence of Yonderboie, a couple of new and interesting productions from the domestic digital underground are slowly changing the overall picture, and although garage rock with its guitar thrashing is back in vogue, even domestic electropop proves that there is something new under the sun.
Balázs Zságer started in Pětikostelí and he also played in Yonderboi&#39;s band, until in the end - perhaps because two pipers cannot fit in one band - he went his own way.
However, with his project (Zagar) and music that combines elements of jazz, electronic dance styles and pop, he only started to break through when he was invited to compose film soundtracks (e.g.
Ferenc Török&#39;s film &quot;Szezon&quot;).
Playing in smaller clubs in the early days, his band became known to a wider audience after wan2 magazine listed their 2002 debut album as one of the fifty most important house records and declared Zagar and Yonderboie to be about the only house trendsetters who could sell and on the West.
Zagar and his band are undoubtedly &quot;on course&quot;, although of course no one asked them if they were happy with this label.
The band responded as they should: they made a new, better album.
The now released album called Cannot Walk Fly Instead may open new paths for them, although the title itself tries to create a connection with the early flights in Pěticostelí.
This is one verse from the composition of Balázs Zságer&#39;s old band there.
The reference to the ethereal, flying would have been appropriate, but next to the ethereal touch of this music, now - in accordance with the spirit, the trend of the time - a louder guitar, the influence of rock and roll appeared.
In these songs, the singer György Ligeti, currently working in England with the group The Puzzle, presented himself at the premiere of the album in Millenáris Park.
The album also produced one real radio hit, thanks to the station mr2 Petőfi, which recently plays popular music from morning to night, the sweeping melodies of Wings of Love, recorded with six local female singers (&quot;Underground Divas&quot;), began to stick.
So everything is fine (?).
The portal hvg.hu interviewed Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: In connection with this new hit, the question arises, to what extent does what you play remain marginal music?
Balázs Zságer: The definition of fringe music doesn&#39;t mean much to me.
In my opinion, there are two different castes of light music; not mainstream and underground, not alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even so-called alternative, underground music can be flat, they don&#39;t say anything, and it can also be created just for the sake of sales, which makes it commercial.
But even a good pop song can stem from an honest inner need.
In this spirit, the attitude, as it is received, works independently of language and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see any difference in the openness of Hungarian and foreign audiences towards your music?
B. Zs.: In foreign countries, especially to the west of us, light music has a greater tradition.
Not only teenagers and people in their twenties go to concerts there, but also older people.
They follow much more the transformations of light music happening around them, because they also consider it a part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What is the role of the audience in your work?
Do you care who listens to your music, where and in what numbers?
B. Zs.: Of course, it feels good that more and more people are coming to our concerts.
But we never made music for the market.
With us, music is not born with a goal, but for a reason.
The role of the audience can be perceived more at concerts, where mutual influence already works, but it is hidden only in the imperceptible changes of the moment.
However, I have noticed that when a person wants to please an audience, from that moment on he ceases to be interesting.
hvg.hu: How far are you going to follow Yonderboi&#39;s example?
He works solo and built his career further west than us.
B. Zs.: We don&#39;t actually follow his path, regardless of the fact that they sometimes try to explain our music that way.
We are more of a team player, relying on each other&#39;s musical presence and letting it unfold.
At first, of course, it was inevitable that our work would be compared to Yonderboi&#39;s compositions, always a few of us would break away from his band and go our separate ways.
hvg.hu: In the mr2 Petőfi chart, the song Wings of Love reached the first place.
Many heard the name Zagar for the first time in connection with this song.
With a more popular style, did you consciously open yourself up to a wider audience?
B.Zs.: We didn&#39;t plan to write a hit that would sell the album.
There&#39;s more to that song.
We intended it as the finale of the album, with which we tried to release the previous sound orgy and more complex themes.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six female singers?
Why is it - what was the main principle?
B.Zs.: The idea was to create such a gospel choir.
Then came the idea to assemble this choir of female soloists of the domestic music scene with good voices.
That&#39;s how this six-member choir came together - that is, Sena, Edin Kutzor, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we later renamed Underground Divas.
hvg.hu: Is this exactly how you intended the song, or did the girls transform it into something?
B.Zs.: The composition had existed for a long time in an instrumental version, when the material for the record was gathered, we thought that something else was needed for this composition.
The sequence of chords beckoned to be joined by a vocal part.
That very night, I sang a tune to it, which the girls later learned.
It all came out almost the first time and very spontaneously.
I remember it being livened up by that, but of course the Divas were needed for that.
It wouldn&#39;t work that energetically with my voice.
hvg.hu: Both on the record and in the concert, it seemed that the girls were in the background.
They don&#39;t have a solo (except for Judy Jay), they don&#39;t have their own part, they sing completely together and they&#39;re not louder than the music, so the music doesn&#39;t just accompany their singing.
They also stood at the back of the stage.
Is that on purpose?
B.Zs.: The fact that they were behind was only due to technical problems.
The fact that we didn&#39;t want to divide solo roles is on the contrary intentional.
That song is also about forgetting our ego a little, where we are from, where we belong, and just letting ourselves be lifted up by those wings, the wings of love.
I wanted others to feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song was born.
hvg.hu: Which one did you work with the most?
B.Zs.: During the composition of the music, not even once, the heavier pieces occurred more during the mixing.
For example, Dorian Gray&#39;s Dilemma, in which I play the concert grand piano, or Rock&#39;n&#39;Roll Goes To The Girls, where the groove didn&#39;t want to work for a long time, then everything slowly found its place, like a jigsaw puzzle.
hvg.hu: Which song from the new album is your favorite?
B.Zs.: That keeps changing with concerts and the fact that I already &quot;released&quot; the record.
Now it&#39;s Prophet Is A Fool, Escape From The Earth and Never The Same.
A treacherous broker risked billions on inferiority
Treacherous fraudster.
