After moving it, the crew began to dismantle the module&#39;s sixty-seven meter solar panels.
And in that one of the panels, unfolding like an accordion, as a result of the cable being pinched, was damaged on an area of almost one meter.
Unfolding was suspended to prevent further damage to the panel.
The astronauts, who were originally supposed to perform a control ascent on Discovery and then go to repair another solar panel whose rotation system had malfunctioned, were forced to attend to the damaged panel.
And it was Scott Parazynski who was chosen to fly to the end of the ship&#39;s robotic arm, added to the station&#39;s arm, and make the repair.
He is one of the best &quot;spacewalkers&quot; (spacewalker) of the American Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA).
