He was assisted by a second &quot;spacewalker&quot; who remained near the buffer chamber, as well as from the inside by other astronauts, among them Peggy Witson, the crew chief.
The tool he used, namely a mini-hockey stick covered with an insulating agent to prevent electric shock on solar panels producing several hundred volts, was invented and &quot;homemade&quot; by astronauts aboard the station.
After the operation was over, Scott Parazynski waited for the panel to be fully disassembled before inventorying his tools and returning to the interior of the station.
