Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense that depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of driving license possession, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, it is necessary to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive an agreed insurance sum of a certain amount for taking responsibility for paying damages in the event of an insured event.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of driving license, type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely you are to have a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, based on checks, insurance companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving and therefore the likelihood that it will have an accident.
As the frequency of trips increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when pricing premiums.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the type of insurance that best matches his policyholder profile.
Here we will show you the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages such as little driving experience and a short driving license when they want to get insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although all risk insurance is ideal for good coverage, there are cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for all risk insurance with a premium discount to get all risk cover but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client&#39;s participation in the payment of the insurance event.
&quot;The part of the claim payment provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the premium price, which will be higher the lower the deductible,&quot; explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other road users, so that the client insures himself against damage caused to other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendation.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to lower your insurance premiums in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the insurance company has.
In contrast, a malus is an increase in the aforementioned base rate.
&quot;Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus&quot;, explains Noguera.
After crossing the twenty-five-year mark, drivers find it easier when they go to get insurance, because the client&#39;s risk index decreases thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks with a discount.
&quot;Young people usually cannot use the previously acquired experience at the time of the accident and even when driving&quot;, assures the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the &quot;newbie&#39;s fear&quot; has already been overcome. .
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which could amount to 300 euros) or, with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
&quot;Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount&quot;, points out Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which amounts to 150 euros) or insurance extended to other road users if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a valid reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best given our personal situation.
