Russia has 53 billionaires with a total fortune of $282 billion, according to Forbes magazine&#39;s list of the richest people.
In addition, the Center for Economic and Financial Research, a leading local institute in the field, released a report on the development of personal wealth in the former Soviet Union, according to which there are 103,000 &quot;second-rate&quot; millionaires in Russia, whose assets add up to 670 billion dollars.
(The World Bank reports that in 2005, 15.8% of Russians lived below the subsistence minimum.)
&quot;There are hundreds of millionaires in Moscow -- and that&#39;s why we&#39;re all here,&quot; said Nicole Marais, sales and marketing representative for London jeweler David Morris.
